	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64340933">Humans are highly driven to be part of a group. Being a social outcast was a death sentence for most of the past several million years. So yes, you can apply the "you had a choice" framing and you're not wrong, but if you want to build a healthy society, you'll look at humans more stochastically and anticipate them following their innate trajectories. In another words, if your city has gang problems then creating more opportunities for sports and hobby/affinity groups might give kids realistic alternatives.</div>
	</div>

