		<div id="comment_body_64341811">Depends on your definition of "supports."<br>
<br>
Officially, many don't. They <i>might</i> prioritize matchmaking two or more people from the same public IP, but unless they have some sort of lobby that can be locked to "invite only" / "friends only", it's a game of Russian Roulette as to whether or not you'll get paired up with the people physically around you.<br>
<br>
<i>Unofficially</i>, practically all of them do. As long as you can control the matchmaking requests and limit them to the LAN. Certain emulators support such methods</div>
